FBIS4-39134 "drsov108_a_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-108 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS U.S., ROK Agree To UN Sanctions Against DPRK U.S., ROK Agree To UN Sanctions Against DPRK LD0306204294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2029 GMT 3 Jun 94 LD0306204294 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] [Text] Moscow June 3 TASS -- U.S. President Bill Clinton had a 30-minute telephone conversation with South Korean President Kim Yong-sam, currently on an official visit to Moscow. During the telephone talks the two leaders agreed that at the moment there is no choice but to press for the U.N. Security Council's sanctions against North Korea to settle the dispute over its nuclear problem, said sources at the South Korean delegation. Clinton told Kim Yong-sam the United States intends to achieve security of South Korea.
